{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to talk about two stories today."},{"time":3000,"text":"One is how we need to use market-based pricing to affect demand"},{"time":10000,"text":"and use wireless technologies to dramatically reduce our emissions"},{"time":14000,"text":"in the transportation sector."},{"time":17000,"text":"And the other is that there is an incredible opportunity"},{"time":19000,"text":"if we choose the right wireless technologies;"},{"time":22000,"text":"how we can generate a new engine for economic growth"},{"time":25000,"text":"and dramatically reduce C02 in the other sectors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"I'm really scared."},{"time":30000,"text":"We need to reduce C02 emissions in ten to fifteen years by 80 percent"},{"time":34000,"text":"in order to avert catastrophic effects."},{"time":37000,"text":"And I am astounded that I'm standing here to tell you that."},{"time":40000,"text":"What are catastrophic effects? A three degree centigrade climate change rise"},{"time":45000,"text":"that will result in 50 percent species extinction."},{"time":50000,"text":"It's not a movie. This is real life."},{"time":53000,"text":"And I'm really worried, because when people talk about cars"},{"time":56000,"text":"-- which I know something about --"},{"time":59000,"text":"the press and politicians and people in this room are all thinking,"},{"time":63000,"text":"\"Let's use fuel-efficient cars.\""},{"time":66000,"text":"If we started today, 10 years from now, at the end of this window of opportunity,"},{"time":74000,"text":"those fuel-efficient cars will reduce our fossil fuel needs by four percent."},{"time":80000,"text":"That is not enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"But now I'll talk about some more pleasant things."},{"time":83000,"text":"Here are some ways that we can make some dramatic changes."},{"time":86000,"text":"So, Zipcar is a company that I founded seven years ago,"},{"time":90000,"text":"but it's an example of something called car sharing."},{"time":93000,"text":"What Zipcar does is we park cars throughout dense urban areas"},{"time":96000,"text":"for members to reserve, by the hour and by the day, instead of using their own car."},{"time":101000,"text":"How does it feel to be a person using a Zipcar?"},{"time":104000,"text":"It means that I pay only for what I need."},{"time":107000,"text":"All those hours when a car is sitting idle, I'm not paying for it."},{"time":111000,"text":"It means that I can choose a car exactly for that particular trip."},{"time":115000,"text":"So, here's a woman that reserved MiniMia, and she had her day."},{"time":119000,"text":"I can take a BMW when I'm seeing clients."},{"time":122000,"text":"I can drive my Toyota Element when I'm going to go on that surfing trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"And the other remarkable thing is it's, I think, the highest status of car ownership."},{"time":136000,"text":"Not only do I have a fleet of cars available to me in seven cities around the world"},{"time":140000,"text":"that I can have at my beck and call,"},{"time":142000,"text":"but heaven forbid I would ever maintain"},{"time":145000,"text":"or deal with the repair or have anything to do with it."},{"time":148000,"text":"It's like the car that you always wanted that your mom said that you couldn't have."},{"time":153000,"text":"I get all the good stuff and none of the bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"So, what is the social result of this?"},{"time":159000,"text":"The social result is that today's Zipcar has 100,000 members"},{"time":163000,"text":"driving 3,000 cars parked in 3,000 parking spaces."},{"time":167000,"text":"Instead of driving 12,000 miles a year, which is what the average city dweller does,"},{"time":170000,"text":"they drive 500 miles a year. Are they happy?"},{"time":174000,"text":"The company has been doubling in size ever since I founded it, or greater."},{"time":178000,"text":"People adore the company. And it's better,"},{"time":183000,"text":"you know? They like it."},{"time":185000,"text":"So, how is it that people went from the 12,000 miles a year to 500 miles?"},{"time":189000,"text":"It's because they said, \"It's eight to 10 dollars an hour and 65 dollars a day."},{"time":194000,"text":"If I'm going to go buy some ice cream,"},{"time":197000,"text":"do I really want to spend eight dollars to go buy the ice cream? Or maybe I'll do without."},{"time":200000,"text":"Maybe I would have bought the ice cream when I did some other errand.\""},{"time":203000,"text":"So, people really respond very quickly to it, to prices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"And the last point I want to make is Zipcar would never be possible without technology."},{"time":211000,"text":"It required that it was completely trivial: that it takes 30 seconds"},{"time":215000,"text":"to reserve a car, go get it, drive it."},{"time":219000,"text":"And for me, as a service provider,"},{"time":221000,"text":"I would never be able to provide you a car for an hour"},{"time":223000,"text":"if the transaction cost was anything."},{"time":225000,"text":"So, without these wireless technologies, this, as a concept, could never happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"So, here's another example. This company is GoLoco --"},{"time":233000,"text":"I'm launching it in about three weeks --"},{"time":235000,"text":"and I hope to do for ridesharing what I did for car sharing."},{"time":239000,"text":"This will apply to people across all of America."},{"time":242000,"text":"Today, 75 percent of the trips are single-occupancy vehicles,"},{"time":245000,"text":"yet 12 percent of trips to work are currently carpool."},{"time":250000,"text":"And I think that we can apply social networks and online payment systems"},{"time":255000,"text":"to completely change how people feel about ridesharing"},{"time":257000,"text":"and make that trip much more efficient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"And so when I think about the future,"},{"time":263000,"text":"people will be thinking that sharing the ride with someone"},{"time":266000,"text":"is this incredibly great social event out of their day."},{"time":269000,"text":"You know, how did you get to TED? You went with other TEDsters."},{"time":272000,"text":"How fabulous. Why would you ever want to go by yourself in your own car?"},{"time":275000,"text":"How did you go food shopping? You went with your neighbor, what a great social time."},{"time":278000,"text":"You know it's going to really transform how we feel about travel,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and it will also, I think, enhance our freedom of mobility."},{"time":287000,"text":"Where can I go today and who can I do it with?"},{"time":289000,"text":"Those are the types of things that you will look at and feel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"And the social benefits:"},{"time":294000,"text":"the rate of single-occupancy vehicles is, I told you, 75 percent;"},{"time":297000,"text":"I think we can get that down to 50 percent."},{"time":300000,"text":"The demand for parking, of course, is down, congestion and the CO2 emissions."},{"time":303000,"text":"One last piece about this, of course, is that it's enabled by wireless technologies."},{"time":308000,"text":"And it's the cost of driving that's making people want to be able to do this."},{"time":311000,"text":"The average American spends 19 percent of their income on their car,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and there's a pressure for them to reduce that cost, yet they have no outlet today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"So, the last example of this is congestion pricing, very famously done in London."},{"time":327000,"text":"It's when you charge a premium for people to drive on congested roads."},{"time":330000,"text":"In London, the day they turned the congestion pricing on,"},{"time":332000,"text":"there was a 25 percent decrease in congestion overnight,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and that's persisted for the four years in which they've been doing congestion pricing."},{"time":340000,"text":"And again, do people like the outcome?"},{"time":344000,"text":"Ken Livingstone was reelected."},{"time":347000,"text":"So again, we can see that price plays an enormous role in people's willingness"},{"time":353000,"text":"to reduce their driving behavior."},{"time":356000,"text":"We've tripled the miles that we drive since 1970 and doubled them since 1982."},{"time":360000,"text":"There's a huge slack in that system;"},{"time":362000,"text":"with the right pricing we can undo that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"Congestion pricing is being discussed in every major city around the world"},{"time":369000,"text":"and is, again, wirelessly enabled."},{"time":371000,"text":"You weren't going to put tollbooths around the city of London"},{"time":373000,"text":"and open and shut those gates."},{"time":375000,"text":"And what congestion pricing is is that it's a technology trial and a psychological trial"},{"time":380000,"text":"for something called road pricing."},{"time":383000,"text":"And road pricing is where we're all going to have to go,"},{"time":385000,"text":"because today we pay for our maintenance"},{"time":387000,"text":"and wear and tear on our cars with gas taxes."},{"time":390000,"text":"And as we get our cars more fuel-efficient,"},{"time":395000,"text":"that's going to be reducing the amount of revenue that you get off of those gas taxes,"},{"time":399000,"text":"so we need to charge people by the mile that they drive."},{"time":403000,"text":"Whatever happens with congestion pricing and those technologies"},{"time":405000,"text":"will be happening with road pricing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"Why do we travel too much?"},{"time":410000,"text":"Car travel is underpriced and therefore we over-consumed."},{"time":413000,"text":"We need to put this better market feedback."},{"time":415000,"text":"And if we have it, you'll decide how many miles to drive,"},{"time":417000,"text":"what mode of travel, where to live and work."},{"time":419000,"text":"And wireless technologies make this real-time loop possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"So, I want to move now to the second part of my story,"},{"time":425000,"text":"which is: when are we going to start doing"},{"time":430000,"text":"this congestion pricing? Road pricing is coming."},{"time":434000,"text":"When are we going to do it? Are we going to wait"},{"time":435000,"text":"10 to 15 years for this to happen"},{"time":437000,"text":"or are we going to finally have this political will to make it happen in the next two years?"},{"time":440000,"text":"Because I'm going to say, that is going to be the tool that's going to turn our usage overnight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"And what kind of wireless technology are we going to use?"},{"time":448000,"text":"This is my big vision."},{"time":451000,"text":"There is a tool that can help us bridge the digital divide,"},{"time":454000,"text":"respond to emergencies, get traffic moving,"},{"time":458000,"text":"provide a new engine for economic growth"},{"time":461000,"text":"and dramatically reduce CO2 emissions in every sector."},{"time":467000,"text":"And this is a moment from \"The Graduate.\" Do you remember this moment?"},{"time":471000,"text":"You guys are going to be the handsome young guy"},{"time":474000,"text":"and I'm going to be the wise businessman."},{"time":477000,"text":"\"I want to say one word to you, just one word.\""},{"time":479000,"text":"\"Yes, sir?\" \"Are you listening?\" \"Yes I am.\""},{"time":485000,"text":"\"Ad-hoc peer-to-peer self-configuring wireless networks.\""},{"time":489000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":493000,"text":"These are also called mesh networks."},{"time":495000,"text":"And in a mesh, every device contributes to and expands the network,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and I think you might have heard a little bit about it before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"I'm going to give you some examples."},{"time":503000,"text":"You'll be hearing later today from Alan Kay."},{"time":505000,"text":"These laptops, when a child opens them up,"},{"time":508000,"text":"they communicate with every single child in the classroom,"},{"time":511000,"text":"within that school, within that village."},{"time":514000,"text":"And what is the cost of that communication system?"},{"time":516000,"text":"Zero dollars a month."},{"time":519000,"text":"Here's another example: in New Orleans,"},{"time":521000,"text":"video cameras were mesh-enabled"},{"time":523000,"text":"so that they could monitor crime in the downtown French Quarter."},{"time":526000,"text":"When the hurricane happened,"},{"time":528000,"text":"the only communication system standing was the mesh network."},{"time":531000,"text":"Volunteers flew in, added a whole bunch of devices,"},{"time":534000,"text":"and for the next 12 months,"},{"time":536000,"text":"mesh networks were the only wireless that was happening in New Orleans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"Another example is in Portsmouth, U.K."},{"time":543000,"text":"They mesh-enabled 300 buses and they speak to these smart terminals."},{"time":547000,"text":"You can look at the terminal"},{"time":549000,"text":"and be able to see precisely where your bus is on the street"},{"time":553000,"text":"and when it's coming, and you can buy your tickets in real time."},{"time":557000,"text":"Again, all mesh-enabled. Monthly communication cost: zero."},{"time":563000,"text":"So, the beauty of mesh networks:"},{"time":566000,"text":"you can have these very low-cost devices."},{"time":568000,"text":"Zero ongoing communication costs. Highly scalable;"},{"time":571000,"text":"you can just keep adding them, and as in Katrina,"},{"time":573000,"text":"you can keep subtracting them -- as long as there's some, we can still communicate."},{"time":577000,"text":"They're resilient; their redundancy is built into this fabulous decentralized design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"What are the incredible weaknesses?"},{"time":583000,"text":"There isn't anybody in Washington lobbying to make it happen --"},{"time":587000,"text":"or in those municipalities, to build out their cities with these wireless networks --"},{"time":590000,"text":"because there's zero ongoing communications cost."},{"time":593000,"text":"So, the examples that I gave you are these islands of mesh networks,"},{"time":597000,"text":"and networks are interesting only as they are big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"How do we create a big network?"},{"time":606000,"text":"Are you guys ready again -- \"The Graduate\"?"},{"time":609000,"text":"This time you will still play the handsome young thing, but I'll be the sexy woman."},{"time":613000,"text":"These are the next two lines in the movie."},{"time":615000,"text":"\"Where did you do it?\" \"In his car.\""},{"time":620000,"text":"So you know, when you stick this idea ... (Laughter)"},{"time":625000,"text":"where would we expect me, Robin Chase, to be thinking"},{"time":629000,"text":"is imagine if we put a mesh-network device"},{"time":631000,"text":"in every single car across America."},{"time":634000,"text":"We could have a coast-to-coast, free wireless communication system."},{"time":640000,"text":"I guess I just want you to think about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"And why is this going to happen? Because we're going to do congestion pricing,"},{"time":648000,"text":"we are going to do road tolls,"},{"time":650000,"text":"gas taxes are going to become road pricing."},{"time":653000,"text":"These things are going to happen."},{"time":655000,"text":"What's the wireless technology we're going to use?"},{"time":657000,"text":"Maybe we should use a good one. When are we going to do it?"},{"time":661000,"text":"Maybe we shouldn't wait for the 10 or 15 years for this to happen."},{"time":664000,"text":"We should pull it forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667000,"text":"So, I'd like us to launch the wireless Internet interstate wireless mesh system,"},{"time":673000,"text":"and require that this network be accessible to everyone, with open standards."},{"time":678000,"text":"Right now in the transportation sector, we're creating these wireless devices --"},{"time":682000,"text":"I guess you guys might have Fast Pass here or Easy Lane --"},{"time":685000,"text":"that are single-purpose devices in these closed networks."},{"time":689000,"text":"What is the point?"},{"time":690000,"text":"We're transferring just a few little data bits"},{"time":692000,"text":"when we're doing road controlling, road pricing."},{"time":694000,"text":"We have this incredible excess capacity."},{"time":696000,"text":"So, we can provide the lowest-cost means of going wireless coast-to-coast,"},{"time":700000,"text":"we can have resilient nationwide communication systems,"},{"time":703000,"text":"we have a new tool for creating efficiencies in all sectors."},{"time":706000,"text":"Imagine what happens when the cost of getting information"},{"time":708000,"text":"from anywhere to anywhere is close to zero."},{"time":711000,"text":"What you can do with that tool: we can create an economic engine."},{"time":715000,"text":"Information should be free, and access to information should be free,"},{"time":718000,"text":"and we should be charging people for carbon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722000,"text":"I think this is a more powerful tool than the Interstate Highway Act,"},{"time":725000,"text":"and I think this is as important and world changing"},{"time":727000,"text":"to our economy as electrification."},{"time":729000,"text":"And if I had my druthers,"},{"time":731000,"text":"we would have an open-source version in addition to open standards."},{"time":735000,"text":"And this open-source version means that"},{"time":740000,"text":"it could be -- if we did a brilliant job of it --"},{"time":742000,"text":"it could be used around the world very quickly."},{"time":747000,"text":"So, going back to one of my earlier thoughts."},{"time":751000,"text":"Imagine if every one of these buses in Lagos was part of the mesh network."},{"time":755000,"text":"When I went this morning to Larry Brilliant's TEDTalk prize"},{"time":760000,"text":"-- his fabulous networks --"},{"time":762000,"text":"imagine if there was an open-source"},{"time":764000,"text":"mesh communications device that can be put into those networks,"},{"time":767000,"text":"to make all that happen."},{"time":769000,"text":"And we can be doing it if we could just get over the fact that"},{"time":773000,"text":"this little slice of things is going to be for free."},{"time":775000,"text":"We could make billions of dollars on top of it,"},{"time":778000,"text":"but this one particular slice of communications needs to be open source."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"So, let's take control of this nightmare:"},{"time":786000,"text":"implement a gas tax immediately;"},{"time":789000,"text":"transition across the nation to road-tolling with this wireless mesh;"},{"time":794000,"text":"require that the mesh be open to all, with open standards;"},{"time":798000,"text":"and, of course, use mesh networks."},{"time":799000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}